{"title_page": "Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3", "text_new": "{{short description|Hungarian conductor}}\n[[File:Zolt\u00e1n-Pesk\u00f3 nel suo camerino al Teatro Donizetti, Bergamo 11-1-2006.jpg|thumb|upright|Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3 in 2006]]\n'''Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3''' (15 February 1937 &ndash; 31 March 2020) was a Hungarian conductor and composer.\n\nPesk\u00f3 was born in Budapest. He studied at the [[Franz Liszt Academy of Music]] with [[Goffredo Petrassi]] and [[Franco Ferrara]], as well as with [[Pierre Boulez]] in [[Switzerland]] in the 1960s.<ref name=\"WZ\" /> He became an assistant under [[Lorin Maazel]] at the [[German Symphony Orchestra, Berlin]]. Pesk\u00f3 served as chief conductor of the {{ill|Orquestra Sinf\u00f3nica Portuguesa|pt}}, the orchestra of the [[Teatro Nacional de S\u00e3o Carlos]] in Lisbon, from 2001 to 2004.<ref name=\"WZ\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musica.gulbenkian.pt/cgi-bin/wnp_db_dynamic_record.pl?dn=db_musica_bios_pt&sn=musica&orn=516|title=Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3 (Maestro Titular)|accessdate=April 30, 2013|language=pt}}</ref><ref name=\"Who\" />\n\nZolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3 died in Budapest on 31 March 2020 at age of 83.<ref name=\"Scala\" /><ref name=\"WZ\" /><ref>[https://fidelio.hu/klasszikus/elhunyt-pesko-zoltan-vilaghiru-magyar-karmester-154174.html Elhunyt Pesk\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n vil\u00e1gh\u00edr\u0171 magyar karmester] {{in lang|hu}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Scala\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.connessiallopera.it/news/2020/zoltan-pesko-il-teatro-alla-scala-ricorda-il-direttore-scomparso/\n| title = Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3: il Teatro alla Scala ricorda il direttore scomparso\n| website = [[La Scala]]\n| date = 1 April 2020\n| language = it\n| accessdate = 2 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Who\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.whoswho.de/bio/zoltn-pesk.html\n| title = Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3\n| website = whoswho.de\n| date = \n| language = de\n| accessdate = 2 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref